knight fellowships class of 2008 ezequiel abiu lopez blanco knight fellowships ezequiel abiu lopez blanco ezequiel abiu lopez blanco knight foundation latin american fellow investigation and special coverage editor clave magazine santo domingo dominican republic study focus economic power and a free press in latin america lopez blanco was born in tlalnepantla mexico and receive his degree from the universidad nacional autonoma de mexico in mexico city he started as a staff writer for the mexican news agency notimex in 1993 in 1997 he became a correspondent for them in the dominican republic and haiti and editor for central america he moved to listin diario as a staff writer and the associated press in the dominican republic as a stringer in 2000 in 2001 he became the chief editor of the national desk for el caribe newspaper he has been at his current magazine clave in the dominican republic since 2005 fellows are listed with original titles and employers from their fellowship year stanford university
